A Lagos High Court sitting in Igbosere, Lagos, yesterday sentenced a man, Oluwaseun Adeniyi, to four years imprisonment for car theft. Adeniyi had entered into a plea bargain with the prosecution and pleaded guilty to an amended count charge of stealing preferred against him by the Lagos State government. Justice Adedayo Akintoye found him guilty as charged and ordered that the sentence should take effect from the day the convict was remanded in prison. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The prosecutor, Mr Babatunde Sunmonnu, had told the court that the defendant committed the offence on July 17, 2016, at Saint Dominicâ€™s Church, Yaba, Lagos, by attempting to steal a Honda Accord car marked KTU 712 BR, property of Mr Benedict Okoro. Sunmonnu said the convict was arrested while in the act by the church members.  Man bags 1 year jail term for robbery Man to spend Xmas in prison for stealing N255,000 recharge cards Driver sentenced to death for robbing former boss